		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Remember, there are no illegal opcodes, only unofficial ones. When the NES encounters one, it doesn't stop or turn off; it does <em>something</em>. Put another way, if a Martian recovered a NES without any software and reverse-engineered it in its entirety, he'd make no distinction between the official and unofficial instructions. They'd all simply be things the CPU did in response to a particular pattern in the opcode.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


